cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SI

This paper deals with supervised learning algorithms and their resilience to discriminatory data perturbations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. The paper also discusses the impact of discrimination on decision-making, which falls under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper proposes a novel method to prevent discrimination, which can be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of protected attributes, which is a topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a method to maximize model accuracy, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
